title: Bug 6322 - All types dialog shows obfuscated classes
description: Bug 6322 - All types dialog shows obfuscated classes. JDK 1.4 includes obfuscated classes (a, a1, b, c, d) etc.
OB: The 'All types' dialog is displaying obfuscated classes from JDK 1.4, such as 'a', 'a1', 'b', 'c', and 'd'.
EB: The 'All types' dialog should only display non-obfuscated classes from JDK 1.4.
SR: To reproduce the issue: 1. Open the 'All types' dialog. 2. Observe that the obfuscated classes from JDK 1.4 are being displayed.
